thread.title_full: Luke Brown and Jake Lever clash heads at Crows training | The Advertiser

author: SCOTT WALSH
title: Luke Brown Jake Lever clash heads at Crows training |
text:
LUKE Brown is expected to be available for Saturday’s crucial clash with Sydney at the SCG despite leaving the training track today following a head knock.
The 22-year-old defender left Adelaide Oval for treatment after clashing heads with Rising Star nominee Jake Lever.
Brown, who racked up 18 disposals during the Crows’ 45-point win over Gold Coast at the weekend, soon returned and was able to finish the session.
MORE: GOODES MAY NOT PLAY
Captain Taylor Walker, this week celebrating his 100-game milestone, said there was no concern over Brown.
“He’ll be fine. I think he just got a knock to the head by Jakey Lever so he’ll be fine,” Walker said. “He finished the whole session.”
Walker, with 37 goals so far this season, said he was keen to return to the form that delivered him 6.5 in the season-opener against North Melbourne. Brown leaves training injured. Photo: Calum Robertson. Source: News Corp Australia
“My form isn’t at a standard for me as an individual but I’m still playing my role for the team just like we ask the other 21 blokes to do,” he said.
“I’ve been working closely with David Teague and Campo (Scott Camporeale) and the other coaches to get back to where I want to be, but I’m just playing my role for the team.”
Walker declined to weigh into the booing debate surrounding Sydney’s Adam Goodes. The Swans dual Brownlow Medallist has taken leave this week following ongoing jeering whenever he goes near the ball, and it is unclear whether he will play the twilight game against the Crows.
“Well, hopefully he doesn’t get too many kicks,” Walker said.
